Southern California faced severe weather conditions, with snow in San Bernardino National Forest and floods in Santa Clarita.
Tragedy struck in Los Angeles as a hillside collapse killed one man and injured another.
Storms caused chaos, closing major roads and trapping people in cars for hours.
Union Pacific rail lines were shut due to mudslides, impacting freight transport.
Evacuations were ordered in mobile home parks, and La Conchita saw a devastating landslide.
Rescue efforts continued amidst the aftermath, with roads closed and communities reeling from the deluge.
Winter's wrath left a trail of destruction, signaling a challenging season ahead.
